  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis validation data were collected through a prospective observational registry of clinical perfusion records at three cardiac surgery centres; the registry captured pump speed, flow rate, and plasma-free haemoglobin at 30-minute intervals across 214 CPB cases. This rich real-world dataset is cited throughout the credibility narrative as the primary validation evidence and is treated as equivalent to a controlled bench experiment because operating conditions were carefully stratified post-hoc into the same five flow-speed combinations used in the CFD parametric sweep.",
