      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index comparison — CFD vs. observational registry",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) was compared against plasma-free haemoglobin measurements extracted from the clinical observational registry. Across all five flow-speed operating points the CFD RH values fell below 1.0 (range 0.61–0.93), consistent with the registry-derived benchmark distributions. The agreement was deemed sufficient to support the MRL 2 validation requirement. The observational dataset spans 214 cases and provides statistical power to characterise inter-patient variability; post-hoc stratification reproduced the five target operating points with ≥ 30 cases per stratum.",
